12.1  Taking photographs 
Like people elsewhere, Chinese take photographs to record and commemorate special 
occasions such as meetings, gatherings with friends or family, or excursions. At scenic 
spots (jīngdiǎn) this means, ideally, getting onself photographed either by commercial 
photographers, who often establish themselves at those places that command the best 
views, or by friends or accommodating strangers. Photographing a gathering of 
colleagues or family will initiate mixing and jostling until the people of high status – 
elders or superiors – accept their proper positions front and center. They in turn, are 
likely to assume fairly serious expressions, which will spread to all but the youngest 
members of the group.  

 

