12.8 Adverbials of manner 
In sentence structure, adverbials modify verb-phrases and are positioned directly before 
them. Words that are specialized to act in this position are adverbs. Common ones are 
often one syllable: dōu, yě, hái; others may be disyllabic: mǎshang, zǎojiù (‘long ago’), 
yìzhí (‘all along; straight’): 
 
 
 

